docs.abstract: Republicans in D.C. just pretend not to see it.
docs.snippet: Republicans in D.C. just pretend not to see it.
docs.lead_paragraph: A lot of Republicans are acting puzzled about Donald Trump’s re-election pitch. “He has no message,” one Republican source told Reuters. “He needs to articulate why he wants a second term,” said another. Some have expressed hope that Trump would find a way to become less polarizing, as if polarization were not the raison d’être of his presidency.

headline.main: Trump’s Re-election Message Is White Grievance

docs.abstract: Junia Joplin, a Baptist pastor in Ontario, asked for acceptance in a sermon: “I want to be the person that God created me to be.” The congregation narrowly voted to terminate her contract.
docs.snippet: Junia Joplin, a Baptist pastor in Ontario, asked for acceptance in a sermon: “I want to be the person that God created me to be.” The congregation narrowly voted to terminate her contract.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last month, the Rev. Junia Joplin told her Baptist congregation in a sermon about the importance of telling the truth without fear of the consequences. And then she revealed a secret truth of her own: She is a transgender woman.

headline.main: Baptist Pastor Is Fired After Coming Out as Transgender
